      • resolveVariable

        public Object resolveVariable(String var)
                       throws javax.servlet.jsp.el.ELException
        Map implicit variable names:

        Vars beginning with 'tag' with following numeric chars are interpreted as a var resulting in the contents of the tag from the message in this context.

        Var names 'fields' and 'tags' (which are equivalent implied var names) return a Map onto this context's message.

        Var name 'storeFMM' return a CRE message store underlying FMM.

        Var beginning with 'serviceFMM' with following chars representing FMM service name return FMM registered as service

        Var beginning with 'uuid' return generated uuid

        Lastly, var names are compared against the well known fix names, such as 'clordid' and result in the contents of the message for that tag.

        Specified by:
        resolveVariable in interface javax.servlet.jsp.el.VariableResolver
        Parameters:
        var - tag name (tag9999) or map name ('fields' or 'tags') or store name ('storeFMM' or 'serviceFMM') or 'uuid'
        Returns:
        tag contents or message Map or FMM or uuid.
        Throws:
        javax.servlet.jsp.el.ELException - - variable couldn't be resolved

      • getUTCTimeToCurrentMilliseconds

        public static long getUTCTimeToCurrentMilliseconds(String utcTime)
                                            throws ParseException
        This function returns the number of milliseconds that have elapse from the provided time to the current time. NOTE: The returned number can be NEGATIVE if the supplied time is in the future.
        Parameters:
        utcTime - The supplied time to compare to the current time. This needs to be in the FIX UTC format.
        Returns:
        The number of milliseconds that have passed since then (or will pass to then, negative value).
        Throws:
        ParseException - This exception is generated when the format of the provided time is not correct.
